    <img src="/assets/images/lentor-gardens-cover.jpg" alt="Lentor Gardens Residences — Kingsford Group's 499-unit OCR launch on a fresh 99-year lease, inside the Lentor Growth Hotspot" loading="eager" decoding="async" />

    <p style="font-style:italic; color:var(--muted);">A ~6 minute read for buyers weighing up the lowest-cost entry into the Lentor precinct before the showflat marketing takes over.</p>

    <div style="background:var(--paper); border-left:4px solid var(--copper); padding:24px 28px; border-radius:0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0; margin:1.5em 0 2em;">
      <strong style="color:var(--teal); display:block; margin-bottom:8px;">TL;DR</strong>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Lentor Gardens Residences</strong> is Kingsford Group&rsquo;s 499-unit OCR launch on a fresh 99-year lease &mdash; secured at <strong>$920 psf ppr, the lowest land cost in the Lentor precinct</strong> (roughly $350 psf below the latest plot awarded). A 7-minute walk to <strong>Lentor MRT (TE5)</strong>, fully inside the <strong>Lentor Growth Hotspot</strong>, with seven future GLS plots within 2&nbsp;km. On the NAVIS PrimeKey Analysis it scores <strong>30 / 40 (75%) &mdash; 3.8 out of 5 stars</strong>: five-star marks on growth hotspot, GLS pipeline, project size and tenure, plus a four-star MRT walk. The two real headwinds: no popular primary school within 1&nbsp;km and a modest ~919-unit MOP cluster nearby. Verdict: <strong>Strong Buy for entry-price-led OCR investors and long-horizon capital-growth buyers</strong>. Less suited to school-driven families and short-term flippers waiting on an upgrader tidal wave. Preview window <strong>4&ndash;14 July 2026</strong> &middot; Sale launch day <strong>18 July 2026</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <p>With 99% of every previous Lentor launch already sold out, the precinct has earned its reputation. The next question is who shows up to define the <em>floor</em> of the cycle &mdash; the launch buyers look back at later and say, <em>that was the entry price the whole estate caught up to</em>.</p>

    <p>That&rsquo;s the role Kingsford Group&rsquo;s <strong>Lentor Gardens Residences</strong> is positioning itself to play. Its land was secured at <strong>$920 psf ppr</strong> &mdash; the lowest in Lentor and approximately $350 psf below the most recently awarded GLS parcel in the same precinct. For buyers, the question isn&rsquo;t whether Lentor will continue to mature. It&rsquo;s whether <em>this</em> launch is buying in cheaper than the market it sits inside.</p>

    <p>Below we walk through the five angles you&rsquo;ll hear from every agent, then run Lentor Gardens through the <a href="/blog/primekey-analysis-introduction">NAVIS PrimeKey Analysis</a> &mdash; the same 8-pillar framework we use to grade any Singapore project on data, not on hype.</p>

